  "method": [
    {
      "heading": null,
      "description": "Dice chicken thighs into little chunks. Throw into a bowl. Grate in a red chilli, your clove of garlic and a large knob of ginger. Add your honey, 3 tbsp of soy sauce and half a can of coconut milk."
    },
    {
      "heading": null,
      "description": "Add a splash of olive oil and mix everything together. Cover and leave in the fridge for 10 minutes to marinate."
    },
    {
      "heading": null,
      "description": "Chop your coriander and cucumber into small chunks and add to a big bowl."
    },
    {
      "heading": null,
      "description": "Dressing time. Into a bowl, add the peanut butter, a tbsp of soy sauce, the juice of a lime, coconut milk and sugar. Keep mixing until you have a smooth, perfect-for-pouring consistency."
    },
    {
      "heading": null,
      "description": "Chicken time. Fry your chicken in batches until it’s cooked through and sticky – pour all of the marinade juices into the pan while cooking."
    },
    {
      "heading": null,
      "description": "Chop your romaine lettuce into small pieces."
    },
    {
      "heading": null,
      "description": "Assembly time. Place the chicken on top of the salad then your coriander and cucumber alongside an extra red chilli if you like it spicy. Scatter a large handful of chopped peanuts over the top, and then pour your peanut butter dressing over everything. Mix together and enjoy."
    }
